1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,560
I don't know how you actually feel.

2
00:00:02,639 --> 00:00:05,600
I just want to do something nice for them.

3
00:00:06,319 --> 00:00:07,856
I'm sorry for being such a terrible leader,

4
00:00:07,880 --> 00:00:09,320
while, in fact,

5
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:11,240
none of them wants to
work under MARS anymore.

6
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:14,399
It seems someone is still going back to the
group's house.

7
00:00:14,479 --> 00:00:17,360
Thame, it's your turn now.

8
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:21,640
Can you help reunite us as a group?

9
00:00:21,720 --> 00:00:24,599
Whether you can or can't, give me a sign.

10
00:00:34,879 --> 00:00:36,616
MR. A, YOU DIDN'T SHOW UP. YOU WENT TO SEE
MR. B, RIGHT?

11
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:37,976
YOU'VE GOT ONLY
ONE CHANCE TO TELL THE TRUTH! @PAWAT.1ANAN

12
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,376
YOUR SCHEDULE TODAY IS FULL OF "MR. B"

13
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:41,080
I GOT IT NOW HOW IMPORTANT MR. B IS TO YOU

14
00:00:47,199 --> 00:00:49,199
You talked about
my story at the alumni gathering?

15
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:50,800
Gotcha.

16
00:00:50,879 --> 00:00:54,239
Does this
mean you're now admitting it's your story?

17
00:00:54,879 --> 00:00:58,680
I'm talking about what
I told you, not my story.

18
00:00:58,760 --> 00:01:01,279
Well, our friends asked why you didn't show
up,

19
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:04,200
so I made something up to keep you looking
good, you know.

20
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:05,920
Ugh, you're just…

21
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,119
So, why didn't you show up,

22
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:10,160
even after promising me so seriously?

23
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:12,119
Tell me.

24
00:01:13,039 --> 00:01:16,160
Work… came up unexpectedly.

25
00:01:20,479 --> 00:01:21,479
Let me help

26
00:01:24,039 --> 00:01:25,080
sew the fabric.

27
00:01:25,679 --> 00:01:27,839
Hey, it's all right.

28
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:31,320
I think you
need to clear things up with a few people.

29
00:01:41,679 --> 00:01:43,199
They must be shocked

30
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,800
since you've never acted this way before.

31
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:55,640
Let me help you.

32
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:05,119
Then, just leave the needle threaded.

33
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:09,920
I'll baste the fabric
for Uncle Joei myself.

34
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:24,320
You know how to do it, right?

35
00:02:25,359 --> 00:02:26,359
I guess I do.

36
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:44,280
Are you in a hurry to go somewhere?

37
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:51,120
It's okay if you have something to do.

38
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:54,160
Well,

39
00:02:54,959 --> 00:02:56,640
since Uncle Joei left the shop like this,

40
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,600
it's probably going to be a while

41
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:03,200
But…

42
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:07,400
if I delay your work,

43
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:08,840
and if it's finished really late,

44
00:03:11,959 --> 00:03:13,440
let me send you home.

45
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:45,280
It's a delicate job, isn't it?

46
00:03:47,079 --> 00:03:48,119
You're being very careful.

47
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:52,840
I have to.

48
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,880
It's a detailed job.

49
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,119
The sandwich tastes good.

50
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,920
If you drop by the shop next time,

51
00:04:09,519 --> 00:04:11,040
can you buy one for me too?

52
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:16,320
Sure,

53
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,640
if there's a chance.

54
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:29,120
Did work come up or a guy, seriously?

55
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,680
Work, of course.

56
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:39,120
Tae, fetch Mick.

57
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,479
There's definitely trouble!

58
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:46,080
What the hell is damn
wrong with you, Thame?!

59
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,080
Hey!

60
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:50,479
Jun, what are you doing?

61
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,400
-What's with you? -Dylan!

62
00:05:51,479 --> 00:05:53,200
-Stop it! -Stop, all of you!

63
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,416
What is so damn wrong with you?

64
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,695
We could have ended this nicely.

65
00:05:55,719 --> 00:05:57,440
What's wrong with you? Huh?

66
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:58,400
Us?!

67
00:05:58,479 --> 00:05:59,479
-Dylan! -Us?!

68
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:01,719
-Dylan. -What the hell is wrong with you?

69
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:03,800
Stop fighting already!

70
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,240
Relax.

71
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:08,159
What's wrong with you guys?

72
00:06:09,359 --> 00:06:10,440
Thame, get up.

73
00:06:12,919 --> 00:06:15,880
You all just keep causing problems!

74
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:18,320
Go. Head to the practice room now.

75
00:06:19,159 --> 00:06:20,719
Ming, Tae, take them there.

76
00:06:22,599 --> 00:06:24,959
Stop doing something insane and head
back to Korea already.

77
00:06:25,919 --> 00:06:27,159
Dylan.

78
00:06:34,719 --> 00:06:37,280
Thame, Miss Pemika asked for you.

79
00:06:37,359 --> 00:06:38,359
Come.

80
00:06:46,719 --> 00:06:48,159
Do you know

81
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:51,240
how much damage you've caused by not going
there?

82
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,320
It's just language training.

83
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:56,560
I can do it here.

84
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:58,919
Explain to that team for me,

85
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,480
telling them I want
to stay here and practice for the concert.

86
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:02,680
Give me some time.

87
00:07:07,599 --> 00:07:10,960
I know what you're trying to do,

88
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,039
but it's going in vain.

89
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:17,799
Fine. If
you need time, I can give you that,

90
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:21,039
but you're not
allowed to practice with the other members.

91
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,599
Huh? But…

92
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:25,320
Use the time I've given you

93
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:28,400
to
Think carefully about what's best for you.

94
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:33,159
In the meantime, unless called, don't come
to the company.

95
00:07:40,239 --> 00:07:41,239
Mick,

96
00:07:42,039 --> 00:07:43,840
have someone drive Thame home.

97
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:47,280
Then, issue the company's statement,

98
00:07:47,359 --> 00:07:49,680
saying that
Thame is sick and needs treatment.

99
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:52,479
All his scheduled jobs
are canceled indefinitely.

100
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,599
You can leave now.

101
00:08:21,599 --> 00:08:22,599
Thank you.

102
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:28,919
Mick asked me to drive you home.

103
00:08:31,159 --> 00:08:32,959
He
Said the traffic is terrible at this hour.

104
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:35,359
He doesn't like getting stuck on
the road for too long.

105
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:36,919
It's a waste of his time for work.

106
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:51,920
MAP SEARCH DESTINATION

107
00:08:53,439 --> 00:08:56,079
Well, where should we go?

108
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:04,640
I'm sorry for making things complicated.

109
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,880
You're in trouble

110
00:09:10,199 --> 00:09:11,480
because of me, right?

111
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:15,920
You? No.

112
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,439
It's all because of me.

113
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:24,280
It's I…

114
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,000
who put you in trouble.

115
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,000
Yeah?

116
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:42,600
I think Thame isn't someone who would plan
and do something alone.

117
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:47,120
I believe someone
must have been instigating this.

118
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:49,480
Do you want me to find out who?

119
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:54,360
You're offering to help like this, so what
do you want from us?

120
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:56,480
I just want the company

121
00:09:57,079 --> 00:09:59,720
to pretend to forget our group's remaining
2-year contract

122
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,360
and allow me to sign with that company,

123
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:06,280
so I can finally start my acting
career that I've always wanted to do.

124
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,680
Deal? It's a win-win situation.

125
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:12,160
Actually, it won't benefit me at all

126
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:14,880
from finding out who that person is.

127
00:10:15,959 --> 00:10:19,760
But what I want is Thame agreeing to go to
Korea.

128
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:24,959
But I think

129
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:27,640
if you can find out who that idiot is,

130
00:10:28,319 --> 00:10:30,680
it will be easier to bring Thame to Korea,
won't it?

131
00:10:33,319 --> 00:10:35,480
Get ready to fire that idiot.

132
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:47,199
That's how scary Jun is.

133
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,959
I won't mess with him for now.

134
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:55,560
How about convincing
the other members to join us first?

135
00:10:57,199 --> 00:10:59,039
It's probably easier to
pressure Jun that way.

136
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,000
No.

137
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:05,840
Jun must be the first one, no matter what.

138
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,079
But you've just mentioned that…

139
00:11:10,719 --> 00:11:12,280
To make this plan successful,

140
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,560
Jun must really be the first one.

141
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:26,360
Jun, it took
you forever! Hurry up and get to shooting.

142
00:11:26,439 --> 00:11:27,839
The director is waiting.

143
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:29,319
Hurry up.

144
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:32,216
- You need to get your makeup done quickly.
- It's because Jun is someone

145
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:33,319
I believe in and trust.

146
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:40,400
-Bro, hello. -Yeah.

147
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,760
-You've just arrived? -Yeah.

148
00:11:43,079 --> 00:11:44,719
Don't you think this location is too hot?

149
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:02,280
I told you to be
here at 6 a.m. Why did you show up at nine?

150
00:12:03,719 --> 00:12:04,560
Eh?

151
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:06,400
Didn't you say nine?

152
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:08,959
See?

153
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:10,959
Six and nine look alike.

154
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:12,695
Since I came at the wrong time,

155
00:12:12,719 --> 00:12:14,879
if the client complains,
who will take responsibility?

156
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,640
Hey, whose snack is that?

157
00:12:21,719 --> 00:12:22,719
Can I take it?

158
00:12:24,839 --> 00:12:26,560
-That one? -Yeah.

159
00:12:29,079 --> 00:12:32,160
Can
you make the products more visible, please?

160
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:33,959
-Sure. -Okay. Thank you.

161
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:38,560
I bought it for you, Gam.

162
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:41,160
Thanks a lot, but next time, you don't have
to.

163
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,319
Don't trouble yourself.

164
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:43,959
I'm sorry I came late.

165
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:46,240
I woke up early to queue up for this,

166
00:12:46,319 --> 00:12:48,040
but tons of people were there.

167
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:49,880
It's really delicious.
I want you to try it.

168
00:12:57,199 --> 00:12:58,199
Let me take some photos.

169
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,599
Sure.

170
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,960
Don't you want some photos with me, too?

171
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:11,360
All right. I'll
ask someone to take them for us.

172
00:13:11,439 --> 00:13:13,439
-Excuse me. -Don't worry. I'll do it.

173
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,599
But he's the one who punched you
and knocked you down.

174
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:31,680
That's him.

175
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:36,400
To be
honest, I don't understand anything at all.

176
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:39,640
Let's put it this way.

177
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,760
I'll figure out a way to talk to him.

178
00:13:42,959 --> 00:13:44,400
How will you do that?

179
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:45,760
I have my own way.

180
00:13:45,839 --> 00:13:50,120
But you'd better stay away from me now

181
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:54,599
because if he suspects
anyone, it will be you.

182
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:58,240
If something urgent is up,

183
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:08,920
call me.

184
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:41,680
You can't outrun the power of the law!

185
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:43,240
Cut!

186
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:48,560
Wow, bro.

187
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:50,880
You nailed it.

188
00:14:51,479 --> 00:14:52,479
Did it hurt?
I'm fine.

189
00:14:53,319 --> 00:14:54,319
No big deal.

190
00:15:00,719 --> 00:15:01,760
Did you record it?

191
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:04,240
I didn't.

192
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:05,280
Show me.

193
00:15:06,920 --> 00:15:08,520
I really didn't record anything.

194
00:15:08,599 --> 00:15:10,760
What kind of documentary director are you?

195
00:15:10,839 --> 00:15:12,439
Why aren't you capturing every moment?

196
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:14,599
So, you want me to film you or not?

197
00:15:15,199 --> 00:15:16,560
Show me, then.

198
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:18,680
I'm curious what you've shot.

199
00:15:26,439 --> 00:15:28,120
But what I want to watch the most

200
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:32,000
is the footage of Thame the other day.

201
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:36,839
Perhaps

202
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:40,079
you're the one who sparked this mess.

203
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,479
Where's that clip?

204
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:51,560
Gotcha.

205
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:53,240
You're acting suspicious.

206
00:15:53,319 --> 00:15:54,680
I'm not.

207
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:56,960
If you scroll through it yourself, how can
you find it?

208
00:15:57,599 --> 00:15:58,680
Let me do that for you.

209
00:15:59,719 --> 00:16:00,719
Oh, really?

210
00:16:01,959 --> 00:16:03,536
You interviewed him, didn't you?
How was it?

211
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:04,640
Did he say anything?

212
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:10,199
Especially if
it's the clip where he vented his feelings,

213
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:15,079
I'm
sure that's what instigated this conflict.

214
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:17,760
Play the clip.

215
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:26,040
A food support truck is here for you, Jun.

216
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:27,839
Wow, Jun.

217
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,920
Your fans are going all out today.

218
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:33,920
They're not his fans, but…

219
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:42,839
Enjoy the food.

220
00:16:43,959 --> 00:16:46,800
FRIED CHICKEN FRIED WITH
CARE, A TREAT TO SHARE

221
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,079
-Thank you. Hello. -Hello.

222
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:49,199
Thank you.

223
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:51,880
Thank you.

224
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:04,159
Jun! Jun! Jun. We're in trouble now.

225
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:06,919
Thame didn't stay home.

226
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:09,095
He refused to pretend to
be sick as the company's statement claimed.

227
00:17:09,119 --> 00:17:10,480
He came to see you here.

228
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:11,560
What should we do?

229
00:17:11,599 --> 00:17:14,280
Eh? Isn't it your job to handle that?

230
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:16,800
Can't you see what I'm doing?

231
00:17:18,359 --> 00:17:19,359
True.

232
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:20,839
Don't interrupt Jun now

233
00:17:20,919 --> 00:17:24,280
because I
think he can't handle Thame either.

234
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:28,480
You said who can't handle Thame again?

235
00:17:28,879 --> 00:17:30,000
You, Jun.

236
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:32,360
You can't handle him.

237
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,720
If you
could, then you must have done it already.

238
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:45,760
I thought you were sick, Thame.

239
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:48,120
- Actually, I'm recovered now.
- He's still sick,

240
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,320
but I think he pushed himself to come out.

241
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:54,120
If there are no more questions, please let
Thame rest.

242
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:57,120
But I pushed myself to
come out because I wanted to see Jun.

243
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,040
Oh my gosh!

244
00:17:58,120 --> 00:17:59,919
Can you say something, Thame?

245
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,000
I brought Jun the food support truck here

246
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:04,280
because I didn't have time to congratulate
Jun

247
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:06,120
both on his movie

248
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,480
and our upcoming album.

249
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,760
Upcoming album?

250
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:12,760
MARS is starting our next chapter,

251
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:14,879
-and now, we're… -Come on, Thame.

252
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:17,120
Don't give away too many spoilers, okay?

253
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,840
-It seems they want some spoilers. -Hey.

254
00:18:18,919 --> 00:18:20,040
Do you want to hear them?

255
00:18:20,120 --> 00:18:21,480
Please. Please go ahead.

256
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:23,720
MARS is definitely coming back soon.

257
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:24,879
We'll bring the song that…

258
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:28,120
Something just bit me.

259
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:31,000
I'm allergic to insects.

260
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:32,800
Do you have any medicine?

261
00:18:33,919 --> 00:18:36,520
Or… can we pause the interview here?

262
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:38,440
We don't need to do that

263
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,520
because when I was sick,

264
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:41,960
I had allergies, too.

265
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:44,016
My symptoms were similar
to what Jun is experiencing now.

266
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:46,120
That's
why I brought him anti-allergy cream today.

267
00:18:49,399 --> 00:18:51,440
That's such a sweet moment!

268
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:52,655
Actually, I knew Jun was sick.

269
00:18:52,679 --> 00:18:54,039
That's why I brought this for him.

270
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:55,560
I know it's going to be tough on set,

271
00:18:55,639 --> 00:18:57,639
and I'm
not sure what the location is like either.

272
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:01,080
But no matter where the location is, see?

273
00:19:01,159 --> 00:19:05,000
Thame is always ready
to support me as an "actor".

274
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:06,536
Otherwise, he wouldn't
bring me both the food support truck

275
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:07,560
and the medicine.

276
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:10,280
This is my true friend,

277
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:13,480
someone who's always ready to
support me on the path I've already chosen.

278
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:16,040
And I've chosen the acting career.

279
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:18,560
I'll definitely become
Jun, Secret Agent 005,

280
00:19:18,639 --> 00:19:20,159
not just Jun from MARS,

281
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:23,560
- but about our upcoming album.
- Whether we have an album or not,

282
00:19:23,639 --> 00:19:24,960
I'll always be the same Jun,

283
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,520
who's not attached to any name.

284
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:28,600
And this is our friendship.

285
00:19:28,679 --> 00:19:32,080
Feed each other fried chicken, please.

286
00:19:32,159 --> 00:19:33,000
Sure.

287
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:34,080
Yum, yum, Thame.

288
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:37,040
Eat up. Yum, yum. Yum, yum.

289
00:19:38,159 --> 00:19:39,440
That's so adorable.

290
00:19:40,159 --> 00:19:43,800
Well, if there are no more
questions, please let Thame rest for now.

291
00:19:43,879 --> 00:19:46,399
Mick, please take care of Thame for me.

292
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:51,520
Hurry up and get him out of here.

293
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:53,159
I need to handle that thing next.

294
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:08,360
You're here to interview me, aren't you?

295
00:20:08,679 --> 00:20:09,840
Why are you sitting here?

296
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:13,399
I'm thinking about the questions.

297
00:20:14,040 --> 00:20:15,240
So, what do you want to ask?

298
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:19,720
Well…

299
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:26,080
Let me see what you interviewed Thame.

300
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:31,520
I'm not done suspecting you.

301
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:33,840
You saw

302
00:20:33,919 --> 00:20:36,919
how I had the upper hand over him, right?

303
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:48,000
To make sure we won't get caught,

304
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:53,080
you should move the
clip where I told the truth to another file

305
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:57,320
because I think someone like him
will definitely check.

306
00:20:59,159 --> 00:21:00,159
Got it.

307
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:04,600
Do we need to finish the whole script?

308
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:06,800
Here?

309
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:13,040
I don't think it'll work.

310
00:21:13,639 --> 00:21:15,040
We might end up getting caught

311
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:18,016
because we haven't returned to the group's
house at all.

312
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:21,200
I think you should cut
the ending where you inserted the interview

313
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:23,520
and just show him the beginning.

314
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:25,159
He's a hot-tempered person,

315
00:21:26,399 --> 00:21:29,480
so if he
only sees that part and feels embarrassed,

316
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:31,280
he'll stop watching.

317
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:36,960
Finally, Jun, your acting career…

318
00:21:40,879 --> 00:21:41,960
Be honest with me.

319
00:21:43,560 --> 00:21:45,040
Why are you so suspicious of me?

320
00:21:46,919 --> 00:21:48,360
I'm just here to earn money.

321
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:51,280
You're the most suspicious one, aren't you?

322
00:21:55,080 --> 00:21:56,080
And…

323
00:21:57,360 --> 00:21:58,560
why are you so mad at Thame

324
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:00,919
for trying to reunite the group?

325
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,320
Do you hate your group that much?

326
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:06,680
So, are you starting the interview already?

327
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:09,960
Well…

328
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:12,080
If you're going to interview me, set up the
camera.

329
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:13,960
And do we have a script?

330
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:17,280
It sounds as if you were going to read it.

331
00:22:19,560 --> 00:22:20,560
Here you are.

332
00:22:25,919 --> 00:22:27,679
All right. I'm ready now.

333
00:22:29,080 --> 00:22:31,320
Let's start. Camera.

334
00:22:31,399 --> 00:22:32,960
Hold on.

335
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:36,520
Well, I want to know

336
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:38,480
if I
can really mention that game center story.

337
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:41,000
I don't know,

338
00:22:41,080 --> 00:22:43,879
but Miss Pemika already approved
the script.

339
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,200
Okay?

340
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:50,480
Camera, speed.

341
00:22:52,679 --> 00:22:54,320
Please say something to Thame.

342
00:22:56,679 --> 00:23:00,720
Thame, I'm
so happy for you that you've come this far,

343
00:23:01,639 --> 00:23:03,240
but it didn't surprise me much

344
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:05,560
because I know you're a talented one.

345
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:13,560
I still remember the first day Pepper, you,
and I started as trainees together.

346
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:17,520
You were
such a good boy that it kind of annoyed me.

347
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:21,496
When you arrived at the building,
you headed straight to the practice room,

348
00:23:21,520 --> 00:23:22,760
without stopping anywhere.

349
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:25,480
During our practice time,

350
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:26,919
you gave it your all.

351
00:23:28,760 --> 00:23:31,320
It was
kind of surprising that we became friends,

352
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,280
especially
since I tricked you into skipping classes.

353
00:23:34,879 --> 00:23:37,280
Hey, let's go to the game center.

354
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,720
Actually, back then,

355
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:05,296
I just wanted to make sure you'd
have a slightly lower score than mine,

356
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:08,240
so I might have a chance to pass
and stay as a trainee in the next round.

357
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:11,840
Hey, don't be tricky.

358
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:22,320
I thought it'd be nice if you got scolded a
little,

359
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:25,399
but we both ended up really getting scolded
together.

360
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:28,879
Are you the
one who made Thame go off track?

361
00:24:31,439 --> 00:24:32,919
But you just…

362
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,200
It was my doing.

363
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:36,040
I asked him to come with me.

364
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:41,000
Don't make excuses for your friend.

365
00:24:41,080 --> 00:24:42,600
It's not an excuse.

366
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,000
I was just too exhausted,

367
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:49,879
so I wanted to do something apart from the
schedule.

368
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:52,879
If you're calling someone a victim,

369
00:24:54,399 --> 00:24:55,919
it's supposed to be Jun.

370
00:24:56,960 --> 00:24:59,679
If
He already knew his score wasn't that okay,

371
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,200
he should have asked me to go with him

372
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:03,840
and then sneaked off to practice alone,

373
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:06,679
not stayed together until the end, right?

374
00:25:10,439 --> 00:25:12,480
You're my first friend in this group,

375
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:15,159
and I'm your
first friend in this group, too.

376
00:25:16,199 --> 00:25:19,320
But from now on, I'm no longer with you,

377
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:22,159
but I want you to remember

378
00:25:23,040 --> 00:25:24,520
that you'll always have me here.

379
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:31,800
Cut.

380
00:25:33,760 --> 00:25:35,560
Let me check if I look handsome.

381
00:25:42,879 --> 00:25:44,080
I'm handsome.

382
00:25:46,360 --> 00:25:48,879
By the way, I have to shoot another scene.

383
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:50,120
Can you wait for me?

384
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:52,615
That slacker Mick
drove the group's van back already,

385
00:25:52,639 --> 00:25:54,280
but he left his car key with me.

386
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:55,360
Drive for me, okay?

387
00:25:55,919 --> 00:25:56,919
I'm too lazy to drive.

388
00:25:58,360 --> 00:26:00,399
If you want my help, why
don't you talk nicely?

389
00:26:01,480 --> 00:26:03,760
What
I do with anyone is my business, isn't it?

390
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:06,679
Also, I'm part of your job.

391
00:26:06,760 --> 00:26:07,920
You must do it anyway, right?

392
00:26:09,439 --> 00:26:10,560
So, wait for me.

393
00:26:10,639 --> 00:26:11,720
I'll get going.

394
00:26:20,679 --> 00:26:23,840
MICK,
I THINK I KNOW FOR SURE WHO THAME'S SPY IS

395
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:32,040
Where do you want me to drop you off?

396
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:34,800
Give me the key. I'll drive myself.

397
00:26:34,879 --> 00:26:37,760
- Eh? You told me to drive for you.
- Come on. Just give it to me.

398
00:26:40,280 --> 00:26:42,480
I just want
someone to talk to, so I won't feel sleepy.

399
00:26:43,040 --> 00:26:44,040
Get in the car.

400
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:56,679
I'll go to Oner first.

401
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:58,480
You've got another job?

402
00:26:58,560 --> 00:26:59,560
Yeah.

403
00:27:00,520 --> 00:27:01,560
What is it?

404
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:04,120
I'm
grabbing you and taking you to Miss Pemika.

405
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:10,696
But no matter what the location is,

406
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:14,439
Thame is always ready
to support me as an "actor".

407
00:27:14,520 --> 00:27:16,240
This is my true friend,

408
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:19,439
someone who's always ready to
support me on the path I've already chosen.

409
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:22,199
JUN

410
00:27:26,320 --> 00:27:29,720
Thame, I've figured out who's been helping
you.

411
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:32,360
Do
You think that interview clip can fool me?

412
00:27:33,159 --> 00:27:35,240
From my work experience,

413
00:27:36,040 --> 00:27:38,400
the length of each member's interview clip
is pretty close.

414
00:27:38,919 --> 00:27:40,600
Mine is 2.30 minutess,

415
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:42,960
but yours is one minute.

416
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:46,760
I think you didn't even
finish that interview,

417
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:49,456
but the two of you might
have talked about something more afterward.

418
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:51,919
Jun, we didn't talk.

419
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,439
Also, the file sequence

420
00:27:57,600 --> 00:27:58,919
is missing two files.

421
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:01,639
I believe you actually
continued the interview,

422
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:04,320
but it got moved out of the camera already.

423
00:28:04,399 --> 00:28:05,760
Where are you?

424
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:06,879
Are you still at the set?

425
00:28:06,960 --> 00:28:08,679
I already left,

426
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:11,040
and I'm not quite sure where this area is.

427
00:28:11,639 --> 00:28:12,639
I'll hang up.

428
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:20,320
PO THERE'S NO SEARCH RESULT FOR "PO"

429
00:28:20,399 --> 00:28:21,879
If something urgent is up…

430
00:28:28,600 --> 00:28:31,360
Jun, let's talk.

431
00:28:33,639 --> 00:28:34,679
Sure thing.

432
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:35,760
Let's talk.

433
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:45,120
What did you say to him?

434
00:28:45,159 --> 00:28:46,800
Why did he agree to come back again?

435
00:28:47,439 --> 00:28:49,239
He
Didn't want to go to Korea from the start.

436
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:51,520
It's not about whether
he wants to go or not.

437
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:53,240
It's just that he must go!

438
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:54,399
Why?

439
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,439
So you can become an actor?

440
00:28:59,679 --> 00:29:01,000
If the group continues,

441
00:29:01,639 --> 00:29:03,399
it's better for you, isn't it?

442
00:29:04,840 --> 00:29:06,280
More people will recognize you.

443
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:09,840
This
isn't about me wanting to become an actor,

444
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:11,840
but it's about Thame.

445
00:29:11,919 --> 00:29:15,159
If he doesn't go, MARS is going to destroy
him.

446
00:29:17,399 --> 00:29:18,399
Huh?

447
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:22,080
How much did he tell you

448
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:25,439
about what he's done for the group?

449
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:30,439
Did he tell you

450
00:29:31,439 --> 00:29:33,720
which contracts he's signed with
the company?

451
00:29:37,959 --> 00:29:40,919
Others might not suspect
it when his new single came out,

452
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:42,280
but I did.

453
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:46,840
The contracts they made him sign to pay off
the group's debt

454
00:29:46,919 --> 00:29:48,479
put him at a disadvantage in every way.

455
00:29:53,959 --> 00:29:55,040
For what?!

456
00:29:56,360 --> 00:29:57,639
Jun, there's no other way

457
00:29:58,840 --> 00:30:00,199
to keep us as a group.

458
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:01,680
If we can't, then just don't do it.

459
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:07,040
But I'm trying to make it possible.

460
00:30:07,120 --> 00:30:08,520
Trust me once, okay?

461
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:19,399
He ended up living his
life carrying four useless people.

462
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:25,439
ARTIST SIGNATURE

463
00:30:32,639 --> 00:30:35,040
When I found out he got an offer
from Korea,

464
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:37,480
I was so damn happy

465
00:30:38,760 --> 00:30:41,080
because he
wouldn't have to carry the others anymore.

466
00:30:45,840 --> 00:30:46,840
But now what?

467
00:30:47,679 --> 00:30:49,120
What did you say to him?

468
00:30:50,360 --> 00:30:52,880
Why did he agree to
come back and do this for the others again?

469
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,679
He should have learned
to be selfish sometimes.

470
00:30:58,879 --> 00:31:01,159
Going
to Korea is the only way for him to get by.

471
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:10,720
Why are you smiling?

472
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:14,240
Are you so scared of getting fired
that you're out of your mind now, huh?

473
00:31:15,959 --> 00:31:16,959
No.

474
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:20,120
I just started to understand

475
00:31:21,439 --> 00:31:24,720
why Thame said you're really important

476
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:28,520
because, actually,

477
00:31:29,040 --> 00:31:31,399
you love him the most.

478
00:31:32,639 --> 00:31:33,480
What?

479
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:35,280
All you said means

480
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:39,639
you want him to have a good future, right?

481
00:31:42,120 --> 00:31:43,720
Do you think I care about him?

482
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:46,480
Stop messing with this thing already.

483
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:48,280
Make him go to Korea,

484
00:31:48,360 --> 00:31:50,360
or none of us will get by.

485
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:52,520
You said

486
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:54,800
you wanted Thame to be selfish, right?

487
00:31:57,560 --> 00:32:02,120
I think what he's doing
now is really selfish.

488
00:32:02,199 --> 00:32:03,639
He's doing this for the others.

489
00:32:05,360 --> 00:32:06,720
How could you see that as selfish?

490
00:32:07,399 --> 00:32:10,719
Thame is doing this for himself.

491
00:32:12,719 --> 00:32:16,320
He's bringing the group
back together entirely for himself,

492
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:18,959
just so he doesn't feel guilty,

493
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:22,576
and to make
up for the leadership he failed to provide.

494
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:23,959
He's doing it

495
00:32:25,399 --> 00:32:27,159
for what he wants to do now,

496
00:32:27,760 --> 00:32:28,919
which is staying as a group.

497
00:32:33,360 --> 00:32:35,320
Since your friend is being this selfish,

498
00:32:37,520 --> 00:32:39,399
don't you want to support him somehow?

499
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:02,080
So, how is it going?

500
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:04,120
Have you caught the traitor yet?

501
00:33:06,159 --> 00:33:07,520
So, it's Po, right?

502
00:33:14,679 --> 00:33:16,800
No. It's not him.

503
00:33:43,919 --> 00:33:44,919
Are you okay?

504
00:33:46,719 --> 00:33:48,360
Relax, Thame.

505
00:33:48,439 --> 00:33:49,480
I'm okay.

506
00:33:51,199 --> 00:33:53,240
-It's true I got caught by Jun, but… -What?

507
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:55,560
Why didn't you call me?

508
00:33:56,320 --> 00:33:57,600
Eh?

509
00:33:58,760 --> 00:34:00,879
If you wanted to help, why didn't you call
me?

510
00:34:00,959 --> 00:34:02,439
I gave you my number,

511
00:34:03,159 --> 00:34:04,520
but you didn't give me yours.

512
00:34:06,679 --> 00:34:07,800
You're right.

513
00:34:09,679 --> 00:34:10,679
Give me.

514
00:34:11,040 --> 00:34:12,040
Give me.

515
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:14,920
Give me your number.

516
00:34:39,520 --> 00:34:40,799
Is everything okay now?

517
00:34:49,679 --> 00:34:51,159
Jun said he wants to talk to you.

518
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:53,719
You'd know where he is.

519
00:35:13,799 --> 00:35:15,360
Why are you this stubborn, huh?

520
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:20,960
And why did you have someone lie
to me that you were the lead in that movie,

521
00:35:23,120 --> 00:35:24,520
when I would find out anyway

522
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:26,279
when it's released?

523
00:35:27,839 --> 00:35:29,400
If I didn't lie,

524
00:35:29,920 --> 00:35:32,240
would you have agreed to go to Korea?

525
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:36,040
Thank you.

526
00:35:38,160 --> 00:35:39,440
Are you out of your mind?

527
00:35:39,520 --> 00:35:40,680
Why did you thank me?

528
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:44,760
Thanks for going back to the group's house.

529
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:47,120
It's you

530
00:35:48,839 --> 00:35:50,000
who watered the tree, right?

531
00:35:50,839 --> 00:35:52,136
Don't think I'm into it or something.

532
00:35:52,160 --> 00:35:53,160
Please, okay?

